HAVERTY FURNITURE COMPANIES, INC. Revenue and Financial Data


   A table for dining, a chair to recline in -- Haverty Furniture Companies fills the bill. Doing business as Havertys, the company sells its own Havertys brand furniture and accessories in the middle- to upper-middle price range. The chain tailors its merchandise to the needs and tastes of local markets, emphasizing "coastal," "western," and "urban" looks in the appropriate region. Havertys also sells bedding from Serta and Tempur Sealy. Furniture accounts for about 80% of the company's sales. The chain has about 120 stores in more than 15 southern and midwestern states. Havertys, which was founded in 1885, is cautiously expanding by enlarging or replacing smaller stores in high-growth markets.
  







